title: Grateful Dead Live at Rhode Island Auditorium on 1971-04-21
description:
Set 1

Casey Jones, Mama Tried, Big Boss Man, Loser, Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat, Hard To Handle, Cumberland Blues, Bird Song, Me And Bobby McGee

Set 2

Bertha, Sugar Magnolia, Good Lovin'-> Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E:Uncle John's Band-> E: Johnny B. Goode

reviews.review_text: Classic 71 show This was always one of my favorites shows to listen in its entirety going back to the late 1980's.  The Dead were playing very well in 1971 and this show is a good example of how solid they were, combining old tunes like The Other One and Hard to Handle with new ones like Wharf Rat, Goin' Down The Road, Uncle John's Band, and others.  Providence, Rhode Island was an underrated hot spot for The Dead for many years, including a ton of shows at Providence Civic Center.  This show, at the 5,200 seat Rhode Island Auditorium, must have been intimate to say the least.  Doubt it was sold out which is INSANE!  If I had a time machine I wouldn't stop the Titanic from sinking but I'd go to THIS SHOW!
Yes sir!..... Me To! this show's been one of my all-time favs. the Audience tapes are nuts. Best H2H.

Incendiary Hard to Handle This one is in the “best ever” conversation right alongside 3/24/71, the various April ‘71 Fillmore East versions, and 8/6/71. I actually think it might be a little hotter than any of those!
